  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ gas 7 and boil a full kettle</p><p>Peel your <strong>potatoes</strong> and chop them into chunky chips, then add them to a pot with plenty of <strong>boiled water</strong> and a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to medium and cook for 10-12 min or until slightly softened</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1629284755307-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1629284755307-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1629284755307-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1629284755307-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1629284755307-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]<strong> </span>vegetable oil</strong> to a deep baking tray (or two!) and put the tray[s] in the oven for 5 min or until the oil is hot</p><p>Peel and finely chop your <strong>shallot[s]</strong></p><p>Combine the <strong>chopped shallot </strong>with your <strong>mayo</strong>, the juice of <strong>half</strong> your <strong>lemon[s]</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> in a  bowl, then give everything a good stir – this is your <strong>lemon mayo</strong></p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1629284758658-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1629284758658-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1629284758658-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1629284758658-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1629284758658-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once done, drain the <strong>softened chunky chips</strong> and reserve the pot, give them a shake in the colander until the edges have fluffed up a little</p><p>Carefully remove the tray[s] of <strong>hot vegetable oil</strong> from the oven and add the <strong>fluffed chunky chips </strong>(do this slowly!)</p><p>Season them with <strong>salt </strong>and turn them a few times until they're fully coated in the oil</p><p>Put the tray[s] in the oven for 30 min or until golden and crisp</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1629284762413-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1629284762413-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1629284762413-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1629284762413-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1629284762413-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, combine your<strong> Marmite</strong> and 80ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[120g]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[160ml]</span> <strong>very cold water </strong>in a bowl, stirring continuously until fully combined – this is your <strong>Marmite water</strong></p><p>Add 60g <span class=\"text-purple\">[90g]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[120g]</span> <strong>flour</strong> to a separate large bowl with <strong>half</strong> of your <strong>red wine vinegar </strong>(save the rest for later!), a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and the<strong> Marmite water</strong></p><p>Stir everything together thoroughly until there are no lumps, then set aside for later – this is your <strong>batter</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
